description.p:
The above-described problem can be solved by the following means.
[1] An information processing apparatus comprising:
a touch-enabled display means;
a lock means that puts the information processing apparatus in standby state and disables all touch gestures except for specified touch gestures including unlock gestures, by locking the information processing apparatus after user logout;
a display control means that performs the following operations: initially displaying a lock screen on the display means, the lock screen indicating that the information processing apparatus is presently locked, the lock screen having a first icon for unlock and one or more second icons each representing a function of the information processing apparatus; and refreshing the lock screen initially displayed on the display means such that the first icon is present at a different position on the lock screen, when a user moves the first icon on the display means;
an unlock means that unlocks the information processing apparatus based on touching and moving the first icon on the lock screen by the user that intends to log in;
a recognition means that recognizes a function as being selected by the user, the function being represented by the one second icon or one of the second icons being present at the position where the user releases the first icon;
a user information obtaining means that obtains user information for identifying the user without requiring user input; and
an authentication means that conducts user authentication on the user with the user information obtained by the user information obtaining means, while the user is moving the first icon,
wherein the display control means changes the lock screen on the display means to a dedicated screen of the user if user authentication is finished by the authentication means while the user is moving the first icon.
[2] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 1, wherein the user information obtaining means obtains the user information from an intra-body communication terminal carried out by the user, by intra-body communication technology enabling communication through a human body as a communication medium.
[3] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 1 or 2, wherein the display control means changes the lock screen to the dedicated screen to display the one or more second icons in a different manner from those on the lock screen.
[4] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 3, wherein, if there is a prohibited function for the authenticated user, the display control means changes the lock screen to the dedicated screen to display the one second icon or one of the second icons in a different manner from that on the lock screen, the one second icon or the one of the second icons representing the prohibited function.
[5] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 3 or 4, wherein displaying in a different manner indicates displaying in a different color, in a different shape, at a different position, or by a combination of two or all of the foregoing.
[6] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 3, wherein, if there is a prohibited function for the authenticated user, the display control means changes the lock screen to the dedicated screen to display one or more of the second icons in a larger size than that on the lock screen, the one or more of the second each icons representing a permitted function for the authenticated user.
[7] The information processing apparatus as recited in any one of Claims 1 to 6, wherein the display control means further displays a third icon on the display means while the user is moving the first icon, the third icon representing a function setting related to the one or more second icons.
[8] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 7, wherein the third icon represents a specific function setting for the authenticated user.
[9] The information processing apparatus as recited in any one of Claims 1 to 8, wherein the display control means reflects the dedicated screen to a background image.
[10] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 9, wherein the background image is a main screen of a function, the function being most likely intended by the user releasing the first icon on the one second icon or one of the second icons.
[11] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 10, wherein the display control means displays the background image in an opaque manner and changes the opacity level of the background image depending on the distance traveled by the first icon being moved.
[12] The information processing apparatus as recited in any one of Claims 1 to 11, wherein the unlock means unlocks the information processing apparatus at a predetermined timing until the user releases the first icon at the position where the one second icon or one of the second icons is present.
[13] The information processing apparatus as recited in Claim 12, wherein, if user authentication is not finished by the authentication means until the user releases the first icon at the position where the one second icon or one of the second icons is present, the display control means displays a user authentication requesting screen on the display means after the user releases the first icon.
[14] The information processing apparatus as recited in any one of Claims 1 to 13, wherein the authentication means conducts user authentication on the user when the user starts moving the first icon.
[15] A display control method of controlling a lock screen displayed, the display control method to be implemented by an information processing apparatus comprising a touch-enabled display means, the display control method comprising:
putting the information processing apparatus in standby state and disable all touch gestures except for specified touch gestures including unlock gestures, by locking the information processing apparatus after user logout;
performing the following operations: initially displaying a lock screen on the display means, the lock screen indicating that the information processing apparatus is presently locked, the lock screen having a first icon for unlock and one or more second icons each representing a function of the information processing apparatus; and refreshing the lock screen initially displayed on the display means such that the first icon is present at a different position on the lock screen, when a user moves the first icon on the display means;
unlocking the information processing apparatus based on touching and moving the first icon on the lock screen by the user that intends to log in;
recognizing a function as being selected by the user, the function being represented by the one second icon or one of the second icons being present at the position where the user releases the first icon;
obtaining user information for identifying the user without requiring user input; and
conducting user authentication on the user with the user information being obtained, while the user is moving the first icon, wherein the lock screen on the display means changes a dedicated screen of the user if user authentication is finished while the user is moving the first icon.
[16] A non-transitory computer-readable recording medium storing a display control program for an information processing apparatus comprising a touch-enabled display means, the display control program for making a CPU of the information processing apparatus execute:
putting the information processing apparatus in standby state and disable all touch gestures except for specified touch gestures including unlock gestures, by locking the information processing apparatus after user logout;
performing the following operations: initially displaying a lock screen on the display means, the lock screen indicating that the information processing apparatus is presently locked, the lock screen having a first icon for unlock and one or more second icons each representing a function of the information processing apparatus; and refreshing the lock screen initially displayed on the display means such that the first icon is present at a different position on the lock screen, when a user moves the first icon on the display means;
unlocking the information processing apparatus based on touching and moving the first icon on the lock screen by the user that intends to log in;
recognizing a function as being selected by the user, the function being represented by the one second icon or one of the second icons being present at the position where the user releases the first icon;
obtaining user information for identifying the user without requiring user input; and
conducting user authentication on the user with the user information being obtained, while the user is moving the first icon, wherein the lock screen on the display means changes to a dedicated screen of the user if user authentication is finished while the user is moving the first icon.

claim.claim-text:
An information processing apparatus (1) comprising:
a touch-enabled display means (22);
a lock means (3) that puts the information processing apparatus in standby state and disables all touch gestures except for specified touch gestures including unlock gestures, by locking the information processing apparatus (1) after user logout;
a display control means (35) that performs the following operations: initially displaying a lock screen on the display means (22), the lock screen indicating that the information processing apparatus (1) is presently locked, the lock screen having a first icon (221) for unlock and one or more second icons (222a)∼(222f) each representing a function of the information processing apparatus (1); and refreshing the lock screen initially displayed on the display means (22) such that the first icon (221) is present at a different position on the lock screen, when a user moves the first icon on the display means (22);
an unlock means (3) that unlocks the information processing apparatus (1) based on touching and moving the first icon (221) on the lock screen by the user that intends to log in;
a recognition means (3) that recognizes a function as being selected by the user, the function being represented by the one second icon or one of the second icons (222a)∼(222f) being present at the position where the user releases the first icon (221);
a user information obtaining means (36) that obtains user information for identifying the user without requiring user input; and
an authentication means (38) that conducts user authentication on the user with the user information obtained by the user information obtaining means (36), while the user is moving the first icon,

wherein the display control means (35) changes the lock screen on the display means to a dedicated screen of the user if user authentication is finished by the authentication means (38) while the user is moving the first icon (221).

A display control method of controlling a lock screen displayed, the display control method to be implemented by an information processing apparatus (1) comprising a touch-enabled display means (22), the display control method comprising:
putting the information processing apparatus (1) in standby state and disable all touch gestures except for specified touch gestures including unlock gestures, by locking the information processing apparatus (1) after user logout;
performing the following operations: initially displaying a lock screen on the display means (22), the lock screen indicating that the information processing apparatus (1) is presently locked, the lock screen having a first icon (221) for unlock and one or more second icons (222a)∼(222f) each representing a function of the information processing apparatus (1); and refreshing the lock screen initially displayed on the display means (22) such that the first icon (221) is present at a different position on the lock screen, when a user moves the first icon (221) on the display means (22);
unlocking the information processing apparatus (1) based on touching and moving the first icon (221) on the lock screen by the user that intends to log in;
recognizing a function as being selected by the user, the function being represented by the one second icon or one of the second icons (222a)∼(222f) being present at the position where the user releases the first icon (221);
obtaining user information for identifying the user without requiring user input; and
conducting user authentication on the user with the user information being obtained, while the user is moving the first icon (221),

wherein the lock screen on the display means (22) changes a dedicated screen of the user if user authentication is finished while the user is moving the first icon (221).

A non-transitory computer-readable recording medium storing a display control program for an information processing apparatus (1) comprising a touch-enabled display means (22), the display control program for making a CPU (31) of the information processing apparatus (1) execute:
putting the information processing apparatus (1) in standby state and disable all touch gestures except for specified touch gestures including unlock gestures, by locking the information processing apparatus (1) after user logout;
performing the following operations: initially displaying a lock screen on the display means (22), the lock screen indicating that the information processing apparatus (1) is presently locked, the lock screen having a first icon (221) for unlock and one or more second icons (222a)∼(222f) each representing a function of the information processing apparatus (1); and refreshing the lock screen initially displayed on the display means (22) such that the first icon (221) is present at a different position on the lock screen, when a user moves the first icon (221) on the display means (22);
unlocking the information processing apparatus (1) based on touching and moving the first icon (221) on the lock screen by the user that intends to log in;
recognizing a function as being selected by the user, the function being represented by the one second icon or one of the second icons (222a)∼(222f) being present at the position where the user releases the first icon (221);
obtaining user information for identifying the user without requiring user input; and
conducting user authentication on the user with the user information being obtained, while the user is moving the first icon,

wherein the lock screen on the display means (22) changes to a dedicated screen of the user if user authentication is finished while the user is moving the first icon.
